He stresses the importance of excluding the presence of bats before maintenance work in the goods, since it is possible that the involuntary destruction of a single nesting site could kill up to 400 females and young animals and wipe out the entire population on site.
Bats are protected and it is illegal to kill, harass, or destroy their nesting sites.
Elisabeth Ferrell, Scottish official of the Bat Conservation Trust, encouraged the population to help.
